•… is design •… pon the •… ine •… owns.The two first obstacles of his design upon the Mine Towns, and which barred his entrance, were the two Towns of Levents and Novigrad, reputed one of the prime places of upper Hungary;
•… ventz
•… ilded. Levents was also well appointed, having in it a Castle manned with couragious Souldiers, and firmed with thick walls, flankers and Turrets, that accordingly gave the enemy a rude and unwelcom entertainment, but their numbers being not to be wearied and no relief to be expected by the besieged, it was yeilded by agreement, and the Articles according to the modern policy of the Turks punctually observed.
